I cant believe anyone who actually likes Star Wars would like this film.  The plot, the acting all of it is just throne together and has no real flow or cohesiveness to it.  There is no character devolpment adn thus we really dont care what happens to anyone, When Anakin fought Obi Wan we cared, Yoda vs the Emperor, Luke vs Vader, heck even the first Rey vs Kylo... in this we get none of it.  How is the Emperor alive? We dont know.  Since when did he have a family? Why is Rey so SUPER powerful? Force skype and force healing may work in comics but they suck in movies.. and force transport objects is freaking DUMB.  The Force Awakens was a great start, Last Jedi ruined it, and this film as much as it tried to fix it didnt do it well.

I was entertained throughout the entire runtime. 
Visually beautiful and some fantastic practical effects. 
Some ideas in the film seemed just thrown in at the last minute after Last Jedi didnt work for fans. So story through the trilogy seems all over the place. But I still enjoyed this one.
amazing and to a beloved story

The movie was not only visually stunning with fantastic music, it was very entertaining and made my fan fantasies come true. Im definitely going to see it at least three more times. If you're like me and dont look critically at movies because you just want to have a good time, then this is an absolute must see!
Loved it. Fitting end to the series.

I absolutely loved this movie! I Was born in 1976 and grew up with Starwars. I have loved something about all of the movies. That being said the Last Jedi failed in so many ways I was afraid to see this movie. From the opening credits all my worries began to disappear. It was an absolute thrill ride and brought back the joy of Starwars. As my 18yr old son says "it's a movie about space wizards, so have fun"
Don't listen to the reviews of the critics. If you are a true Star Wars fan you'll enjoy this movie. It's not perfect, but no Star Wars movie is. It's a very satisfying ending to the saga.

I enjoyed this movie a lot. As a star wars fan since I was really young, this movie did a very good job of bringing the saga together. I've read EU content and consider myself a more old school fan, and I was very happy to see the dark empire style movie that was shown. Props to JJ Abrams for finally giving Rey a good end to her arc, and giving good background to her strong force sensitivity.
A classic final to a classic saga that deserve respect of all of us
